definitions: describing electromagnetic radiation with wavelengths shorter than violet light but longer than X-rays
relating to or using ultraviolet radiation, especially for its germicidal or fluorescent properties
examples: The ultraviolet rays from the sun can damage your skin
Hospitals use ultraviolet lamps to sterilize medical equipment
Scientists discovered ultraviolet markings on the bird's feathers
The club's ultraviolet lighting made white clothes glow brightly

definitions: relating to or affecting the navel or umbilical cord that connects a fetus to the placenta
describing a crucial connection or lifeline between two things, like a supply line or cable
examples: The umbilical cord provides nutrients to the developing baby
Doctors carefully cut the umbilical connection after birth
The spacecraft remained attached by an umbilical cable during testing
The island depends on an umbilical ferry link to the mainland

definitions: encompassing or covering many different elements, groups, or categories under one system or organization
providing overarching protection or coverage like an umbrella shields from rain
examples: The umbrella organization represents dozens of smaller charities
They created an umbrella term to describe all these conditions
The military provides umbrella air coverage for ground operations
The company offers umbrella insurance policies for extra protection

definitions: not embarrassed, disconcerted, or ashamed by something others might find awkward or improper
examples: She showed unabashed enthusiasm for the amateur theater production
His unabashed love of pop music surprised his classical friends

definitions: without any reduction in intensity, force, or strength; continuing at full power
examples: The storm continued unabated throughout the night
Public interest in the trial remains unabated after three weeks

definitions: not shortened or condensed; containing the complete and original text or content
examples: She prefers reading unabridged versions of classic novels
The library stocks both abridged and unabridged dictionaries

definitions: not able to be accepted, allowed, or approved because it fails to meet required standards
examples: Such rude behavior is completely unacceptable in our workplace
The committee found the proposal's budget projections unacceptable

definitions: having no companion or escort; traveling, existing, or performing alone
performed without instrumental accompaniment, especially referring to singing or solo instruments
examples: Unaccompanied minors require special assistance when flying
She felt nervous walking unaccompanied through the dark streets
The choir sang several unaccompanied pieces during the concert
He played an unaccompanied violin sonata with remarkable skill

definitions: not officially recognized, authorized, or certified by a professional or educational accrediting body
examples: Students from unaccredited schools may have trouble transferring credits
The unaccredited laboratory's test results weren't accepted by regulators

definitions: not familiar or used to something through lack of experience or practice
examples: She felt unaccustomed to the formal atmosphere of the embassy
His hands, unaccustomed to manual labor, quickly developed blisters

definitions: not recognized, admitted, or accepted as valid, existing, or having contributed to something
examples: Her contributions to the project remained unacknowledged for years
The family's unacknowledged tensions finally surfaced during the reunion

definitions: not decorated or embellished; plain, simple, and without ornamental additions
examples: The room's unadorned walls gave it a minimalist appearance
She preferred the unadorned truth to diplomatic euphemisms

definitions: not mixed or diluted with any different or extra elements; pure and complete
examples: The chef insists on using unadulterated olive oil in cooking
Her face showed unadulterated joy when she heard the news

definitions: not influenced, changed, or harmed by something that affects others
genuine, natural, and unpretentious in manner or behavior without artificial airs
examples: The mountain village remained unaffected by modern development
Coastal areas were unaffected by the inland drought conditions
Her unaffected charm made everyone feel comfortable and welcome
Despite his wealth, he maintained an unaffected speaking style

definitions: not officially attached to or connected with an organization, group, or particular body
examples: Many unaffiliated voters choose candidates based on individual merit
The research was conducted by scientists unaffiliated with pharmaceutical companies

definitions: feeling no fear or anxiety; brave and confident in facing something
examples: She remained unafraid despite the threatening phone calls
Children who are unafraid of water learn to swim more quickly

definitions: needing or having no assistance, support, or help from others or devices
examples: He managed to walk unaided just weeks after the accident
The star is too faint to see with the unaided eye

definitions: not broadcast on television or radio; kept from public viewing or hearing
not exposed to fresh air or ventilation; kept closed and stuffy
examples: Several unaired episodes were later released on streaming platforms
The network decided to keep the controversial interview unaired
The unaired rooms smelled musty after months of being closed
Unaired bedding can develop an unpleasant odor over time

definitions: remaining in the original state without any changes, modifications, or amendments
examples: The historical documents have remained unaltered for centuries
She wanted her grandmother's recipe to remain completely unaltered

definitions: relating to Lancaster, its people, or especially the House of Lancaster in English history
examples: The Lancastrian forces wore red roses during the civil war
She speaks with a distinctive Lancastrian accent from northwest England

definitions: relating to Laos, its people, culture, or language in Southeast Asia
examples: Traditional Lao cuisine features sticky rice as a staple food
She studied Lao language and culture at the university

definitions: relating to or characteristic of Laos, its inhabitants, or their language and customs
examples: The Laotian government promotes sustainable tourism in rural areas
Laotian silk weaving is recognized for its intricate patterns

definitions: relating to people of Latin American origin or descent, especially those living in the United States
examples: The city celebrates Latino heritage month with festivals and parades
Latino voters represent a growing demographic in many states

definitions: relating to Latvia, its people, language, or culture in the Baltic region
examples: Latvian folk songs are an important part of cultural heritage
She learned Latvian to communicate with her grandmother's family

definitions: relating to Lebanon, its people, culture, or things originating from this Middle Eastern country
examples: Lebanese cuisine is famous for its mezze and fresh ingredients
The Lebanese community has contributed significantly to the city's culture

definitions: relating to the Levant region of the eastern Mediterranean, including its cultures and peoples
examples: Levantine Arabic has distinct features from other Arabic dialects
The museum displays ancient Levantine pottery and trade goods

definitions: relating to Liberia, its people, or culture in West Africa
examples: The Liberian flag closely resembles the American flag in design
Liberian English has unique expressions influenced by indigenous languages

definitions: relating to Libya, its people, culture, or things from this North African country
examples: Ancient Libyan rock art provides insights into prehistoric life
Libyan oil reserves play a major role in the economy

definitions: relating to Carl Linnaeus or his system of classifying and naming organisms in biology
examples: The Linnaean system uses binomial nomenclature for species names
Modern taxonomy has evolved beyond the original Linnaean classifications

definitions: relating to the Swedish botanist Linnaeus or his biological classification system
examples: The Linnean Society promotes the study of natural history
Scientists still use Linnean principles in naming new species

definitions: relating to Lithuania, its people, language, or culture in the Baltic region
examples: Lithuanian is considered one of the oldest living Indo-European languages
Traditional Lithuanian amber jewelry is popular with tourists

definitions: not open to more than one interpretation; having only one possible meaning that is clear
examples: The contract terms were unambiguous about payment deadlines
She gave an unambiguous answer when asked about her intentions

definitions: fully in agreement with all people involved sharing the same opinion or vote
examples: The jury reached a unanimous verdict after brief deliberation
The board made a unanimous decision to approve the merger

definitions: happening or arriving without warning, prior notice, or announcement
examples: The inspector made unannounced visits to ensure compliance
Her parents arrived unannounced while she was having a party

definitions: not responded to or addressed; remaining without a reply or solution
examples: Several important questions remained unanswered after the meeting
Her emails went unanswered for weeks during his absence

definitions: not expected or predicted; coming as a surprise without prior anticipation
examples: The project faced unanticipated delays due to supply shortages
An unanticipated inheritance changed their retirement plans completely

definitions: not acknowledging or expressing regret for actions or statements others find offensive
examples: She remained unapologetic about her controversial artistic choices
His unapologetic attitude after the mistake angered his colleagues

definitions: not attractive, inviting, or interesting; failing to appeal to senses or emotions
examples: The restaurant's unappealing decor drove away potential customers
The job offer was unappealing due to long hours

definitions: not carrying or equipped with weapons or arms for defense or attack
examples: The security guards were unarmed and relied on communication skills
Police confirmed the suspect was unarmed during the arrest

definitions: lacking armor or protective covering; vulnerable to attack or damage without defensive plating
examples: The unarmored vehicles were vulnerable to roadside explosives
Medieval archers targeted unarmored parts of knights' bodies

definitions: unable to be attacked, questioned, or defeated; absolutely secure or irrefutable in position
examples: Her logic was unassailable and convinced even the skeptics
The fortress occupied an unassailable position on the mountaintop

definitions: not allocated, designated, or given to any particular person, purpose, or category
examples: Several unassigned parking spaces are available for visitors
The unassigned tasks were distributed among new team members

definitions: performed or achieved without help, aid, or support from others or devices
examples: The toddler took her first unassisted steps yesterday morning
He completed an unassisted triple play in baseball history

definitions: not pretentious or arrogant; modest and unpretentious in manner or appearance
examples: Despite her success, she remained unassuming and approachable
The restaurant's unassuming exterior concealed its excellent cuisine

definitions: not fastened, joined, or connected to something else physically or organizationally
not involved in a committed romantic relationship; single and available
examples: The unattached garage can be converted into a workshop
Several unattached cables need to be connected properly
She enjoys being unattached and focusing on her career
Most unattached people at the event were hoping to meet someone

definitions: not able to be reached, achieved, or acquired despite efforts; beyond one's grasp
examples: Perfect happiness seemed an unattainable goal for the pessimist
The championship remained unattainable despite their best efforts

definitions: not supervised, watched, or cared for; left alone without anyone present
examples: Never leave children unattended near the swimming pool
The unattended luggage was removed by security personnel

definitions: not pleasing or appealing to look at or consider; lacking attractive qualities
examples: The building's unattractive facade discouraged potential buyers
Rising crime made the neighborhood unattractive to young families

definitions: not having official permission or approval; done without proper authority
examples: Unauthorised access to the database resulted in data theft
The company prohibits unauthorised copying of proprietary software

definitions: not having official permission or approval; lacking proper authority or consent
examples: Unauthorized personnel cannot enter the restricted area
The bank detected several unauthorized transactions on her account
